{"word":"H6080 - עָפַר - ʻâphar - aw-far' - Cast","slug":"H6080","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עָפַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻâphar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-far'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cast"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E2;&#x05E4;&#x05E8; - &#x201B;a&#x0302;phar</b> - <i>aw-far'</i><p/>A primitive root; meaning either to <i>be gray</i> or perhaps rather to <i>pulverize</i>; used only as denominative from <a href=\"#/H6083\">H6083</a>, to <i>be dust: - </i>cast [dust]."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6083\">H6083</a>"}]}